<br />

<br />
It is actually still a pretty big discrepency.
<br />

<br />
Let's look at a base, base case between a lvl 70 mage and druid.  No special AAs, no special foci, no specializations.
<br />

<br />
Straight up chain nuking:  Tie between mage and druid.  A druid can match a mage nuke for nuke using glitterfrost.  Unless, we use Bolt of Jerikor whereupon we out dps them.  Add a 100+ dps for pets and the disparity becomes even larger.
<br />

<br />
Mage Nuking, Druid Nuking + DoTs:  Once again the mage comes out ahead with nuking alone.
<br />

<br />
Nuke  |  cast time (w/ recast)  |  dmg  |  max DPS
<br />

<br />
Vengeance of the Sun (druid DoT 70) |  7.5 s  |  2060  |  274  dps
<br />
Wasp Swarm (druid DoT 68)  |  8.25 s  |  2136  |  258 dps
<br />
Glitterfrost (druid DD 70)  |  8.6 s  |  2132  |  247 dps
<br />
Star STrike (mage DD 70)  |  8.6 s  |  2132  |  247 dps
<br />
Bolt of Jerikor (mage bolt 66)  |  9.25  |  2751  |  297 dps
<br />

<br />
The easiest way to look at a DoT is to think of it as a DD with a really long recast.  So, if you take a look at the theoretical max dps a druid could do it would be the average over a period of time of Vengeance of the Sun (274 dps) + Wasp Swarm (258 dps) and Glitterfrost (247 dps).  With the latter spell being chained until Vengeance of the Sun refreshes and the DoT cycle can begin anew.  Even with the highest DoTs from a pure data standpoint they cannot match the dps by the Bolt of Jerikor.  Or if we did not use BoJ and instead used Star Strike, the dps difference between Vengeance of the Sun and Star Strike is so nominal that a pet can easily overtake it.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=653282" target=_blank>Casala</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1023548" target=_blank>Aderyn- cleric bot</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.hneguild.com" target=_blank>Heaven and Earth</a>
<br />
Saryrn</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
