			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok for starters, I did not say ALL raiding mages have poor pet control, and secondly I will rephrase what I said.
<br />

<br />
Raiding Mages USED to have poor pet control because thier pets were banned.  I have no clue what servers you guys play on, but until pet faction change and pet hold, pets were banned from any raid that had AE mobs, such as dragons and the like (this was before rampage) and in any encounter where it was proven that people couldn't control thier pets (through being afk, not paying attention etc.)  Over the past couple of years, this isn't the case anymore.  I have friends that still complain that sometimes pets are banned because mage_04's or beastlord_97's pet went after a mob and got the puller killed, or worse.
<br />

<br />
I am NOT asking for a pet that can go and easilly tank pofire like nothing, I AM asking for a pet that allows me to solo what gives me good exp WITHOUT burning my whole mana bar.
<br />

<br />
I don't have the best gear (I broke 5k mana recently when I dinged 66) and I only have DPoC focus.  I have better gear then many but not nearly as good gear as those who are in the end game (I'm not even elemental flagged.)  I never said a raid mages pet should be as good as a casuals.  I said that we shouldn't need to get focus items to make our pets able to do what they are SUPPOSED to.
<br />

<br />
I see some of you saying "well I don't have any trouble with pet tanking" then 2 or three words later "60-something shaman bot" appears. Sure, our pets can tank with SLOW, especially when it is fully shammy buffed and mobs are crippeled.  I'm talking about soloing, as in, just you and Geker, no shaman bots, no duoed clerics.
<br />

<br />
Another thing, it's all fine and dandy that your CoWind pet can tank certain things, we should've had the OoW line of pets in at the latest the LDoN era.  They are the pets we need for PoP, also focus and pet dps and general needs to be rescaled.
<br />

<br />
Mages ARE disgruntled about some beastlord abilities, that is evident by every other post I see on this board- a mage yelling about a beastlord, and visa versa, hell its on this thread too now.  I don't think mages should be envious or disgruntled at beastlords, but they are.
<br />

<br />
Finally, druid and wizzy dps.  Wizards are great for burst damage, and I never said they shouldn't ahve cold nukes, all I'm saying is that if they are going to limit us to magic and fire, fire being are most damaging, to at least give us a resist edge on them, or stop making a large number of mobs in each expansion highly fire resistant.<br />_________________<br /><img src="http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v53/keeeen/EQ%20pics/KenSig.jpg" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
<a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=441622' target='_blank'>Inspect Me</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
